## Overview  
**Dr. Dana A. Williams** is a leading scholar in African American literature and Africana Studies, currently serving as the **Dean of the Graduate School at Howard University**. She is widely recognized for her contributions to African American literary criticism, cultural studies, and the promotion of Black intellectual traditions. Dr. Williams has dedicated her career to advancing the study and appreciation of African American literature and the broader Africana experience.

